How does the state catch one of the mafia bosses today?

01:30:56.255 --> 01:30:58.135
Even though he's a killer

01:30:58.135 --> 01:30:59.718
still, you can't hold anything against them

01:30:59.718 --> 01:31:03.923
So they catch them with tax-income crimes.

01:31:03.923 --> 01:31:09.183
Ibn Taymiyyah had many enemies for different reasons

01:31:09.183 --> 01:31:13.385
Ibn Taymiyyah was outspoken and strongly expressed his views.

01:31:13.385 --> 01:31:15.671
Like Ibn Abd al-Salam.

01:31:15.671 --> 01:31:17.490
And he insults the Sultan,

01:31:17.490 --> 01:31:22.433
although he was friends with some great Mamluks.

01:31:22.433 --> 01:31:29.009
Ibn Taymiyyah had a somewhat strong personality.

01:31:29.009 --> 01:31:33.867
Sometimes he used to say things that raised many political enemies.

01:31:33.867 --> 01:31:36.820
But when they try to judge him with anything,

01:31:36.820 --> 01:31:39.550
and he was a part of a long and wide progress,

01:31:39.550 --> 01:31:46.030
They won't isolate all the other problems and judge him in this one thing

01:31:46.030 --> 01:31:49.001
No. There were a lot of complications.

01:31:49.001 --> 01:31:53.016
Al-Hallaj was killed for a reason

01:31:53.016 --> 01:31:57.872
other than the one for which he was being tried.

01:31:57.872 --> 01:32:05.100
He fell into a situation where it allowed the minister to end him.

01:32:05.100 --> 01:32:08.039
They had other reasons.

01:32:08.039 --> 01:32:10.870
They apprehended him for a minor claim and murdered him.

01:32:10.870 --> 01:32:18.641
You don't see that in all the states of Umayyad, Abbasid, and Ottoman

01:32:18.641 --> 01:32:21.018
there was no interference at all?

01:32:21.018 --> 01:32:26.652
Shari‘a prevailed as the supreme master over the sultans.

01:32:26.652 --> 01:32:28.951
This is also a very firm point.

01:32:28.951 --> 01:32:35.177
Shari‘a is the one that decided what the political structures were

01:32:35.177 --> 01:32:38.190
and governance in Islam as well.

01:32:38.190 --> 01:32:45.493
You said: Sufism is the overall explanation of Shari‘a.

01:32:45.493 --> 01:32:51.310
also: Islam relies on two dimensions, Sufism and Shari‘a.

01:32:51.310 --> 01:32:53.703
What do you mean by Sufism?

01:32:53.703 --> 01:33:03.956
Sufism is the care of soul-body.

01:33:03.956 --> 01:33:07.212
You add a dash between soul and body.

01:33:07.212 --> 01:33:09.334
They are considered one word.

01:33:09.334 --> 01:33:14.222
The soul-body is there to educate the legitimate personality.

01:33:14.222 --> 01:33:20.292
Notice that Shari‘a started with some principles of Sufism.

01:33:20.292 --> 01:33:22.045
If look at Sufism,

01:33:22.045 --> 01:33:25.794
for example, fasting was in the Shari‘a from the beginning

01:33:25.794 --> 01:33:29.049
Not just Shari‘a, but since the inception of Islam.

01:33:29.049 --> 01:33:35.182
It is in many verses in the Holy Quran.

01:33:35.182 --> 01:33:39.743
It's also one of the five Pillars of Islam.

01:33:39.743 --> 01:33:42.272
What is the meaning of fasting?

01:33:42.272 --> 01:33:53.790
Today, we haven't started to understand 0.001% of what fasting and hunger mean

01:33:53.790 --> 01:33:56.447
in educating human subjectivity.

01:33:56.447 --> 01:33:58.305
There is a lot of work.

01:33:58.305 --> 01:34:03.708
I have students that I try to guide to study the meaning of fasting and hunger.

01:34:03.708 --> 01:34:09.326
And how they relate to creating a unique subjectivity.

01:34:09.326 --> 01:34:11.345
It's very important.

01:34:11.345 --> 01:34:15.929
What is special about Sufism is that

01:34:15.929 --> 01:34:21.474
it takes humility, fasting, noiselessness, and silence,

01:34:21.474 --> 01:34:25.916
and also the Maqamat and all other conditions

01:34:25.916 --> 01:34:31.286
and you take them to form it into effective formula

01:34:31.286 --> 01:34:33.445
in the person's actions

01:34:33.445 --> 01:34:39.858
to make him the ideal example of the legitimate self.

01:34:39.858 --> 01:34:43.391
This is why Al-Ghazali wrote the Revival of Religious Sciences.

01:34:43.391 --> 01:34:47.530
The Revival of Religious Sciences is the summary

01:34:47.530 --> 01:34:52.383
of Islamic efforts from the previous two centuries or more.

01:34:52.383 --> 01:34:56.063
Al-Ghazali died in 505 AH.

01:34:56.063 --> 01:34:58.633
1111 AD.

01:34:58.633 --> 01:35:04.033
Sufism began in Baghdad, mainly.

01:35:04.033 --> 01:35:07.123
It had spread to other places

01:35:07.123 --> 01:35:10.515
since the beginning of the third century AH.

01:35:10.515 --> 01:35:15.244
At the end of the third century AH, its features were almost clear.

01:35:15.244 --> 01:35:19.374
In the fourth century, it evolved.

01:35:19.374 --> 01:35:24.475
At the time of al-Ghazali in the fifth century, it had a full shape

01:35:24.475 --> 01:35:28.471
and was very effective, but not as much later on.

01:35:28.471 --> 01:35:31.966
There were many great Sufis during this period.

01:35:31.966 --> 01:35:39.087
Abu Nasr as-Sarraj and many others had voices that were loud and recognized.

01:35:39.087 --> 01:35:43.874
Revival of Religious Sciences of al-Ghazali

01:35:43.874 --> 01:35:49.934
combined one leg of Sufism and one of Shari‘a in one mold.

01:35:49.934 --> 01:35:57.471
Islam stands on the legs of Sufism and Shari‘a more than any other.

01:35:57.471 --> 01:36:02.045
I call them the central domains.

01:36:02.045 --> 01:36:08.662
Shari‘a and Sufism are two central domains in Islam.

01:36:08.662 --> 01:36:12.860
Let's talk about mathematics.

01:36:12.860 --> 01:36:16.440
It's a secondary domain

01:36:16.440 --> 01:36:21.442
because it supports the central domain and serves its objectives.

01:36:21.442 --> 01:36:30.607
In today's world, art is a secondary domain that serves capitalism.

01:36:30.607 --> 01:36:37.534
Of course, it has a lot of artistic things, artistic taste, and beauty.

01:36:37.534 --> 01:36:39.326
Aesthetics, as they say

01:36:39.326 --> 01:36:46.859
Of course, when I painted these paintings, it wasn't for capitalistic reasons; I didn't want to sell them.

01:36:46.859 --> 01:36:49.887
They are mine; I made them to hang around my house.

01:36:49.887 --> 01:36:52.740
A lot of artists are like that.

01:36:52.740 --> 01:37:01.217
In the end, the power of the central domain flips the priorities of the secondary domain.

01:37:01.217 --> 01:37:05.348
If I died for example,

01:37:05.348 --> 01:37:12.907
and my daughter knows how to market them

01:37:12.907 --> 01:37:18.535
and people find these paintings beautiful.

01:37:18.535 --> 01:37:22.207
Then they buy them and resell them.

01:37:22.207 --> 01:37:26.780
Today, Picasso or other great ones,

01:37:26.780 --> 01:37:28.912
Where can you find their paintings?

01:37:28.912 --> 01:37:37.442
They are present on a yacht that a Russian billionaire bought for his girlfriend.

01:37:37.442 --> 01:37:40.612
He bought her one of Picasso's

01:37:40.612 --> 01:37:45.762
Imagine how Picasso painted his paintings

01:37:45.762 --> 01:37:49.253
And in Madrid or mainly in Paris,

01:37:49.253 --> 01:37:52.021
between 1905 until he died.

01:37:52.021 --> 01:37:55.010
Imagine what he was thinking about while painting

01:37:55.010 --> 01:37:57.549
and how his art became part of Capitalism.

01:37:57.549 --> 01:38:04.540
Insurance companies buy them and put them in the halls of huge buildings in Tokyo.

01:38:04.540 --> 01:38:09.778
What is the difference if the art didn't serve Capitalism

01:38:09.778 --> 01:38:13.880
and served a central domain like Islam?

01:38:13.880 --> 01:38:16.099
What is going to be different about it?

01:38:16.099 --> 01:38:19.425
If the central domain was a moral domain,

01:38:19.425 --> 01:38:23.270
and that is a new topic in this discussion

01:38:23.270 --> 01:38:26.036
we could go on for hours discussing it.

01:38:26.036 --> 01:38:29.914
So, if the central domain is a moral domain,

01:38:29.914 --> 01:38:37.675
it doesn't matter how the secondary domains transform.

01:38:37.675 --> 01:38:41.040
In the end, it will serve the moral domain.

01:38:41.040 --> 01:38:45.839
And the moral domain is always a humane domain.

01:38:45.839 --> 01:38:51.121
It's humane because it cares about what's inside a human.

01:38:51.121 --> 01:38:54.471
It cares about his soul first, then his body.

01:38:54.471 --> 01:38:57.147
To his soul, his nafs (self), and his body.

01:38:57.147 --> 01:38:59.532
Shari‘a and Sufism

01:38:59.532 --> 01:39:04.594
are fundamentally central domains.

01:39:04.594 --> 01:39:10.755
By the way, Shari‘a is not essentially a legal apparatus.

01:39:10.755 --> 01:39:16.361
When I say 'legal apparatus', I use modern terminology.

01:39:16.361 --> 01:39:21.030
Does this mean that the words legal or law (qanoon) do not exist in Islamic heritage?

01:39:21.030 --> 01:39:23.791
No, it was the Turkish Qanoon that emerged

01:39:23.791 --> 01:39:26.546
as a weak link or thread

01:39:26.546 --> 01:39:31.377
to increase the punishments, for example, for adultery and prostitution.

01:39:31.377 --> 01:39:37.355
However, it came to prove the basic principles of Sharia

01:39:37.355 --> 01:39:40.424
They called it law, but it's not like the law of today.

01:39:40.424 --> 01:39:49.796
Today, The Law is the legal rulings issued by the states.

01:39:49.796 --> 01:39:55.259
They are purely political and statutory issues.

01:39:55.259 --> 01:39:59.512
Ok, based on your book about the state

01:39:59.512 --> 01:40:02.218
you mentioned in your book 'Sharī'a'

01:40:02.218 --> 01:40:05.334
that the Ottoman state is the first state

01:40:05.334 --> 01:40:08.126
to choose a madhhab for itself.

01:40:08.126 --> 01:40:10.278
The Hanafi Madhhab

01:40:10.278 --> 01:40:14.236
What is the effect of choosing one madhhab on the state?

01:40:14.236 --> 01:40:15.769
And on legislation?

01:40:15.769 --> 01:40:21.317
Why did the Ottomans do it while others before them didn't?

01:40:21.317 --> 01:40:23.468
(True. Why didn't it happen before?)

01:40:23.468 --> 01:40:26.424
Before them, the Mamluks were in Egypt and Syria.

01:40:26.424 --> 01:40:29.726
They had four of them, not just one or two.

01:40:29.726 --> 01:40:33.534
They thought that all four madhhabs should have a presence.

01:40:33.534 --> 01:40:36.315
They have a chief justice for each one.

01:40:36.315 --> 01:40:41.915
The Ottomans refused and picked the Hanafi Madhhab only.

01:40:41.915 --> 01:40:44.726
But you have to look

01:40:44.726 --> 01:40:47.215
at what domain

01:40:47.215 --> 01:40:49.878
the Ottoman state was established in

01:40:49.878 --> 01:40:52.091
The Ottomans

01:40:52.091 --> 01:40:55.877
with the Safavid state

01:40:55.877 --> 01:40:58.393
and the Mughal state

01:40:58.393 --> 01:41:01.546
they were three Islamic empires

01:41:01.546 --> 01:41:05.861
that were some of the most powerful empires of that time.

01:41:05.861 --> 01:41:10.075
They were called the Gunpowder Empires.

01:41:10.075 --> 01:41:12.691
The Gunpowder Empires

01:41:12.691 --> 01:41:21.571
They were the first to import and use gunpowder and old handguns.

01:41:21.571 --> 01:41:28.146
But this name is not a matter of describing the use of weapons only.

01:41:28.146 --> 01:41:33.641
Rather, it is a description of new Islamic and non-Muslim empires

01:41:33.641 --> 01:41:38.642
that started to work differently in their political rule.

01:41:38.642 --> 01:41:40.619
There was a difference.

01:41:40.619 --> 01:41:43.979
From the the beginning of Islam to the Mamluks

01:41:43.979 --> 01:41:46.909
there was some kind of continuity.

01:41:46.909 --> 01:41:50.316
There was somewhat of a jump.

01:41:50.316 --> 01:41:53.895
It was small compared to the one in the 19th century.

01:41:53.895 --> 01:42:01.064
It was a small jump before the Ottomans rose.

01:42:01.064 --> 01:42:03.991
And the Safavids and others.

01:42:03.991 --> 01:42:07.073
But why?

01:42:07.073 --> 01:42:11.071
All of these developments

01:42:11.071 --> 01:42:13.328
happened in what is called

01:42:13.328 --> 01:42:17.715
World history.

01:42:17.715 --> 01:42:21.930
World history is a field of study.

01:42:21.930 --> 01:42:24.605
It means the whole history of the world

01:42:24.605 --> 01:42:26.852
If a historian studies history

01:42:26.852 --> 01:42:31.060
of Aleppo in Syria or a village near it.

01:42:31.060 --> 01:42:34.149
This is a short history.

01:42:34.149 --> 01:42:37.212
But he could study Islam

01:42:37.212 --> 01:42:42.234
or the Islam of Mamluks or Umayyads.

01:42:42.234 --> 01:42:44.432
World history

01:42:44.432 --> 01:42:49.458
covers the colloquial map

01:42:49.458 --> 01:42:53.042
to study the actions of the states and how they affect each other

01:42:53.042 --> 01:42:56.536
and their dealings with each other, and who affected who.

01:42:56.536 --> 01:43:01.385
When you only study a specific village

01:43:01.385 --> 01:43:06.438
such as the marriage practices in a village in northern China,

01:43:06.438 --> 01:43:09.304
that's fine and good for you,

01:43:09.304 --> 01:43:11.440
but you don't know much.

01:43:11.440 --> 01:43:13.158
Because you are confined to it.

01:43:13.158 --> 01:43:15.646
Unless you start comparing and seeing

01:43:15.646 --> 01:43:19.883
It is always necessary to compare with others.

01:43:19.883 --> 01:43:24.788
Comparative studies are a new science in the human mind.

01:43:24.788 --> 01:43:27.960
If I stay without it, my mind will be different.

01:43:27.960 --> 01:43:31.023
And when I import it into my mind and start comparing

01:43:31.023 --> 01:43:35.198
my mind will evolve immensely.

01:43:35.198 --> 01:43:37.621
The comparison is very important.

01:43:37.621 --> 01:43:41.286
My whole scientific project, from beginning to end,

01:43:41.286 --> 01:43:44.239
whenever I cover an area

01:43:44.239 --> 01:43:48.274
I go to another area similar to it, parallel to it, in another civilization

01:43:48.274 --> 01:43:50.098
and I see how it's doing.

01:43:50.098 --> 01:43:56.417
This is to understand the relativism of the first field that I studied

01:43:56.417 --> 01:43:58.698
which is Shari‘a for me.

01:43:58.698 --> 01:44:02.650
Comparisons are very important.

01:44:02.650 --> 01:44:06.846
What was the question again, please?

01:44:06.846 --> 01:44:09.956
(I got distracted there for a second.)

01:44:09.956 --> 01:44:15.329
It was about the Ottomans choosing the Hanafi Madhhab.

01:44:15.329 --> 01:44:21.673
We lost track while discussing a methodological topic.

01:44:21.673 --> 01:44:25.497
The Ottomans came as a reaction,

01:44:25.497 --> 01:44:27.659
part of it was a reaction,

01:44:27.659 --> 01:44:30.364
for the first European expansions.

01:44:30.364 --> 01:44:36.146
When the Ottomans rose, the Renaissance in Europe was happening.

01:44:36.146 --> 01:44:39.760
What was happening in Italy at that time,

01:44:39.760 --> 01:44:43.691
and they were very close to them,

01:44:43.691 --> 01:44:49.117
What was happening in Italy and Spain at that time was very important.

01:44:49.117 --> 01:44:54.050
Part of the Ottomans in Europe and the other in Asia.

01:44:54.050 --> 01:44:56.442
This is before their occupation of Arab states

01:44:56.442 --> 01:44:58.971
like Egypt, Palestine, and Syria.

01:44:58.971 --> 01:45:02.410
When they started to develop,

01:45:02.410 --> 01:45:05.801
and when you look at who those Ottoman Sultans were,

01:45:05.801 --> 01:45:11.802
The vast majority of the Ottoman sultans' mothers

01:45:11.802 --> 01:45:17.179
who strongly ruled with their children and husbands

01:45:17.179 --> 01:45:20.933
The women of the Royal Palace in Islam

01:45:20.933 --> 01:45:24.841
had great importance and influence in governance.

01:45:24.841 --> 01:45:27.105
For example, Suleiman the Magnificent

01:45:27.105 --> 01:45:28.607
Who was his wife?

01:45:28.607 --> 01:45:30.724
She was a Christian Ukrainian.

01:45:30.724 --> 01:45:34.771
He married her, and she converted to Islam and had children.

01:45:34.771 --> 01:45:36.961
She became his ruling partner..

01:45:36.961 --> 01:45:39.312
He is Suleiman the Lawgiver or Suleiman the Magnificent

01:45:39.312 --> 01:45:42.185
When you go to visit Sulaymaniyah in Istanbul,

01:45:42.185 --> 01:45:45.935
You'd say he was one of the greatest men, and he really was,

01:45:45.935 --> 01:45:48.717
but his wife was very important too.

01:45:48.717 --> 01:45:51.222
And his children as well.

01:45:51.222 --> 01:45:54.640
Who was their mother? It's Roxelana.

01:45:54.640 --> 01:45:59.056
The Ottomans sent spies to Europe

01:45:59.056 --> 01:46:04.295
to see the latest European cannon design and build one like it in Istanbul.

01:46:04.295 --> 01:46:09.907
If you study Ottoman military history

01:46:09.907 --> 01:46:14.617
you'll find that it was filled with stories like it.

01:46:14.617 --> 01:46:16.496
Not only that,

01:46:16.496 --> 01:46:21.157
they hired Austrian and Swedish engineers

01:46:21.157 --> 01:46:26.827
they paid them a lot more than they make in Europe to get them to Istanbul

01:46:26.827 --> 01:46:30.528
to help them build this new kind of cannon.

01:46:30.528 --> 01:46:34.832
They knew a great deal about what Europeans were doing.

01:46:34.832 --> 01:46:36.727
So, what did they do about it?

01:46:36.727 --> 01:46:42.176
There is a main reason Europe became modern.

01:46:42.176 --> 01:46:44.682
The modernity we know about

01:46:44.682 --> 01:46:47.239
It's Political Centralization.

01:46:47.239 --> 01:46:51.586
Everything became concentrated in one place.

01:46:51.586 --> 01:46:54.237
They call it Centralization in English.

01:46:54.237 --> 01:46:56.552
Everything is built in one place.

01:46:56.552 --> 01:47:00.495
Because European history originated with a king.

01:47:00.495 --> 01:47:03.940
They used to call him the absolute ruler.

01:47:03.940 --> 01:47:06.338
He was the legislator.

01:47:06.338 --> 01:47:11.672
In Monarchy, the king says: I speak on behalf of God.

01:47:11.672 --> 01:47:16.217
It was the absolute ruler in Europe, or absolutism.

01:47:16.217 --> 01:47:21.810
The king thinks he is God's representative on earth.

01:47:21.810 --> 01:47:24.711
He is the law.

01:47:24.711 --> 01:47:28.587
As Louis XIV said.

01:47:28.587 --> 01:47:34.278
And he represents God on Earth and speaks for him.

01:47:34.278 --> 01:47:39.784
The Ottomans couldn't do something like that.

01:47:39.784 --> 01:47:43.977
Because of Islam and the Islamic society.

01:47:43.977 --> 01:47:48.983
If they said something like that, all the Ottoman family would be exiled.

01:47:48.983 --> 01:47:52.041
And all the Islamic peoples will rise to stop it.

01:47:52.041 --> 01:47:54.788
But this is what they did instead.

01:47:54.788 --> 01:47:59.632
They thought that having four Madhhabs was complicated and too much trouble.

01:47:59.632 --> 01:48:01.607
And there were some troubles.

01:48:01.607 --> 01:48:04.164
When you have a plurality of sects

01:48:04.164 --> 01:48:06.433
and this much freedom of law

01:48:06.433 --> 01:48:08.343
you'll have to pay its price.

01:48:08.343 --> 01:48:09.623
What was the price?

01:48:09.623 --> 01:48:12.648
We'll talk about it in a little while.

01:48:12.648 --> 01:48:20.006
They wanted to take three of the madhhabs to a lower position.

01:48:20.006 --> 01:48:21.623
Not in a negative way.

01:48:21.623 --> 01:48:27.515
And they will be managed and ruled by the Hanafi madhhab

01:48:27.515 --> 01:48:33.054
The chief Justice will be appointed in Istanbul.

01:48:33.054 --> 01:48:34.902
Let's say the Chief Justice of Egypt.

01:48:34.902 --> 01:48:37.770
So he goes from Istanbul to Cairo.

01:48:37.770 --> 01:48:43.012
While in Cairo, Alexandrea or any other

01:48:43.012 --> 01:48:48.536
He appoints judges according to who lives in this country.

01:48:48.536 --> 01:48:55.121
If there were too many Hanbalis, he would give them more than one Hanbali judge.

01:48:55.121 --> 01:48:58.822
The same is true for Shafii and the rest.

01:48:58.822 --> 01:49:01.845
It's not that they disappeared,

01:49:01.845 --> 01:49:06.011
but the Ottoman Shari‘a Administration

01:49:06.011 --> 01:49:09.171
was centralized in Istanbul.

01:49:09.171 --> 01:49:12.634
And Istanbul produced the Hanafi madhab only.

01:49:12.634 --> 01:49:17.664
The chief justice is Hanafi.

01:49:17.664 --> 01:49:21.683
The chief justice is the beholder.

01:49:21.683 --> 01:49:26.075
The beholder is the one who examines things.

01:49:26.075 --> 01:49:32.133
How have this idea and this change affected the Muslim world?

01:49:32.133 --> 01:49:39.866
It wasn't a qualitative change.

01:49:39.866 --> 01:49:42.641
It is a quantitative change.

01:49:42.641 --> 01:49:47.958
And of course, if the quantity gets too much, it becomes a quality.

01:49:47.958 --> 01:49:54.020
Quality and quantity are not two different things.

01:49:54.020 --> 01:50:00.191
If you had a white paint bowl

01:50:00.191 --> 01:50:03.186
and you put one red dot in it

01:50:03.186 --> 01:50:05.173
and you mix it, it will still be white.

01:50:05.173 --> 01:50:06.714
With a second drop it will still be white.

01:50:06.714 --> 01:50:09.607
With 100 drops, it will be mostly white.

01:50:09.607 --> 01:50:12.150
If you add a cup, it will turn pink.

01:50:12.150 --> 01:50:17.103
But if you add 10 times the amount of red paint, it will be completely red.

01:50:17.103 --> 01:50:20.503
Quality and quantity are connected.

01:50:20.503 --> 01:50:29.875
The Ottoman Empire had a kind of quantity that didn't become quality.

01:50:29.875 --> 01:50:35.639
However, this quantity,

01:50:35.639 --> 01:50:43.588
later in the nineteenth century, after the year 1826, it became important.

01:50:43.588 --> 01:50:50.207
These changes, for example, centralize the Shari‘a administratively in the Hanafi madhab.

01:50:50.207 --> 01:50:56.635
And dividing the Sanjaks and the empire in a certain way

01:50:56.635 --> 01:50:59.437
and collect taxes in a certain way.

01:50:59.437 --> 01:51:04.978
They were trying to do them all in a successful way, but for what?

01:51:04.978 --> 01:51:07.213
They were learning from Europe.

01:51:07.213 --> 01:51:10.478
It's not that they were scared; Europe was actually very weak.

01:51:10.478 --> 01:51:15.216
But when you see that your neighbor invented a new weapon,

01:51:15.216 --> 01:51:17.797
and even if you are 100 times stronger than him,

01:51:17.797 --> 01:51:20.267
you would want to know what he is doing.

01:51:20.267 --> 01:51:22.060
From a position of power.

01:51:22.060 --> 01:51:25.184
So they used to take things from Europe.

01:51:25.184 --> 01:51:30.796
One of them was facilitating the administration of the empire by this method.

01:51:30.796 --> 01:51:33.431
In 1826

01:51:33.431 --> 01:51:35.523
for the first time

01:51:35.523 --> 01:51:40.377
the Ottoman empire found itself

01:51:40.377 --> 01:51:43.015
in a very severe predicament.

01:51:43.015 --> 01:51:49.005
Since the 1777-80

01:51:49.005 --> 01:51:51.589
until a little more over 1800

01:51:51.589 --> 01:51:53.904
and a lot more later on

01:51:53.904 --> 01:51:56.574
but I am focusing on the era before 1826

01:51:56.574 --> 01:52:00.840
The Russian Tsarist

01:52:00.840 --> 01:52:06.200
was handing them crushing defeat after crushing defeat.

01:52:06.200 --> 01:52:10.351
In almost every war, the Russians win.

01:52:10.351 --> 01:52:13.947
At first, the Ottomans were winning,

01:52:13.947 --> 01:52:17.782
and they took the now-disputed areas between Ukraine and Russia.

01:52:17.782 --> 01:52:22.087
like Crimea

01:52:22.087 --> 01:52:26.086
What happened in this period

01:52:26.086 --> 01:52:30.513
is that Ottomans lost war after war

01:52:30.513 --> 01:52:33.396
So much so that it ruined it economically.

01:52:33.396 --> 01:52:37.052
It began internal reforms, and they reformed armies.

01:52:37.052 --> 01:52:39.758
All of their military apparatus

01:52:39.758 --> 01:52:41.518
it happened before 1826

01:52:41.518 --> 01:52:45.818
but in 1826, the first phase of army reform had ended.

01:52:45.818 --> 01:52:47.900
This is very important.

01:52:47.900 --> 01:52:52.478
But there was a radical change

01:52:52.478 --> 01:52:56.222
it added to the quality, not just the quantity.

01:52:56.222 --> 01:53:01.841
For the first time in Islamic history,

01:53:01.841 --> 01:53:07.976
the state says that large and important Islamic Awqaf (Endowments)

01:53:07.976 --> 01:53:11.740
belongs to the capital of Istanbul.

01:53:11.740 --> 01:53:15.155
In Islamic history, Awqaf have always been independent

01:53:15.155 --> 01:53:19.883
It has its budgets, its economy,

01:53:19.883 --> 01:53:22.577
and its management, they were supervised by a judge.

01:53:22.577 --> 01:53:27.277
Every year, he checks the books, accounts, and the rest.

01:53:27.277 --> 01:53:31.547
He leaves what's theirs to them.

01:53:31.547 --> 01:53:35.904
But in 1826,

01:53:35.904 --> 01:53:39.494
All the Awqaf send their income to the capital

01:53:39.494 --> 01:53:42.692
and the capital decides how much goes back to the Awqaf.

01:53:42.692 --> 01:53:46.513
Not every Awqaf has its own budget any more.

01:53:46.513 --> 01:53:49.752
Its budget became subject to state intervention.

01:53:49.752 --> 01:53:54.385
And things started to get worse and worse for Shari‘a from that day on.

01:53:54.385 --> 01:53:59.158
If you took the Awqaf from the hands of Shari‘a, you killed Shari‘a.

01:53:59.158 --> 01:54:01.736
This is how it worked at that time.

01:54:01.736 --> 01:54:04.658
At the beginning, Shari‘a didn't need the Awqaf.

01:54:04.658 --> 01:54:06.256
But later on,

01:54:06.256 --> 01:54:09.215
at the start of the fifth century,

01:54:09.215 --> 01:54:12.657
there were Nizamiyyas in Baghdad

01:54:12.657 --> 01:54:14.900
established by Nizam al-Mulk

01:54:14.900 --> 01:54:17.227
The famous Vizier of Seljuk Empire

01:54:17.227 --> 01:54:20.213
after that, it was like a flood

01:54:20.213 --> 01:54:23.193
of Awqaf were built in Islamic history.

01:54:23.193 --> 01:54:25.501
It was everywhere you look.

01:54:25.501 --> 01:54:30.026
By the way, when the crusaders entered

01:54:30.026 --> 01:54:36.072
they learned to create their colleges

01:54:36.072 --> 01:54:38.814
in Bologna, Paris, and London

01:54:38.814 --> 01:54:41.947
From the Muslims.

01:54:41.947 --> 01:54:46.992
Columbia University is an updated version,

01:54:46.992 --> 01:54:54.167
or a modern version of the Nizamiyyas Madrasa system in Baghdad.

01:54:54.167 --> 01:55:00.754
Ok, this was the first intervention

01:55:00.754 --> 01:55:04.451
The Ottomans took Awqaf to themselves

01:55:04.451 --> 01:55:06.681
They controlled Awqaf.

01:55:06.681 --> 01:55:11.873
After about 20 years,

01:55:11.873 --> 01:55:14.634
it entered the stage of the so-called Tanzimat.

01:55:14.634 --> 01:55:19.805
In my personal opinion, the Tanzimat came in 1826, not 1856.

01:55:19.805 --> 01:55:21.355
What are these Tanzimat?

01:55:21.355 --> 01:55:25.352
The Tanzimat was the beginning

01:55:25.352 --> 01:55:29.402
of Westernization of infrastructure

01:55:29.402 --> 01:55:31.707
for the Ottoman Empire

01:55:31.707 --> 01:55:35.400
Westernization in the sense that it becomes like the West.

01:55:35.400 --> 01:55:41.391
Islamic laws have started to be left on the sidelines.

01:55:41.391 --> 01:55:48.077
They imported crime and penal codes from Germany

01:55:48.077 --> 01:55:53.105
and other laws from France and Italy.

01:55:53.105 --> 01:55:58.576
They used them instead of the Islamic laws.

01:55:58.576 --> 01:56:03.983
The first step was taken in 1852.

01:56:03.983 --> 01:56:07.599
But the Awqaf and their confiscations,

01:56:07.599 --> 01:56:10.633
in the meaning I described

01:56:10.633 --> 01:56:13.958
and not the traditional way

01:56:13.958 --> 01:56:17.115
This was in 1826

01:56:17.115 --> 01:56:22.213
In 1826, it was the first step that cleared the way

01:56:22.213 --> 01:56:25.466
to blow up

01:56:25.466 --> 01:56:29.320
a section of Islamic Shari‘a and Islamic laws

01:56:29.320 --> 01:56:31.857
in the fifties of the nineteenth century.

01:56:31.857 --> 01:56:36.843
They then started establishing European-style law schools.

01:56:36.843 --> 01:56:39.930
They created a new generation

01:56:39.930 --> 01:56:45.720
that is related to Western law and the application of Western law.

01:56:45.720 --> 01:56:47.648
Excuse me?

01:56:47.648 --> 01:56:50.228
And here is where the codification of Sharia took place?

01:56:50.228 --> 01:56:52.503
Codifying of Sharia happened later

01:56:52.503 --> 01:56:54.873
but this was the start.

01:56:54.873 --> 01:56:57.804
The 'Mecelle' is somewhat of a codification.

01:56:57.804 --> 01:57:00.741
But we'll talk about codification maybe later

01:57:00.741 --> 01:57:02.810
 because it is a little more complicated than that

01:57:02.810 --> 01:57:06.913
Let's go back to 1826 to see what happened to Awqaf.

01:57:06.913 --> 01:57:13.326
All of the Awqaf income went to Istanbul.

01:57:13.326 --> 01:57:16.373
Istanbul returns a little bit of it

01:57:16.373 --> 01:57:18.760
and they take the rest

01:57:18.760 --> 01:57:21.920
to spend it on wars and other things.

01:57:21.920 --> 01:57:26.871
These new law schools

01:57:26.871 --> 01:57:31.604
train people to graduate

01:57:31.604 --> 01:57:34.461
and later hold strong positions.

01:57:34.461 --> 01:57:37.151
But at the same time,

01:57:37.151 --> 01:57:42.279
the money that went back to traditional scholars who studied Shari‘a,

01:57:42.279 --> 01:57:49.649
it was reduced to 20%–15% of what they used to get.

01:57:49.649 --> 01:57:52.392
I'll give you a small example:

01:57:52.392 --> 01:57:56.163
Imagine that China occupied America

01:57:56.163 --> 01:58:02.061
whether it was a direct occupation or the kind that forced their will

01:58:02.061 --> 01:58:05.256
because colonization has many methods

01:58:05.256 --> 01:58:10.421
and you look for the one who makes or produces

01:58:10.421 --> 01:58:19.910
the fertile grounds and the froth of the law in America

01:58:19.910 --> 01:58:23.055
They are the main educators

01:58:23.055 --> 01:58:25.824
in the well-known law schools

01:58:25.824 --> 01:58:30.001
which are Harvard, Yale, Columbia

01:58:30.001 --> 01:58:33.018
and other 4 or 5 schools.

01:58:33.018 --> 01:58:36.948
If we look at Harvard and Yale,

01:58:36.948 --> 01:58:41.401
How much do the professors make there?

01:58:41.401 --> 01:58:45.194
About $300,000 and 500,000

01:58:45.194 --> 01:58:48.090
These are their wages.

01:58:48.090 --> 01:58:52.421
This is the average.

01:58:52.421 --> 01:58:57.651
Imagine if China creates new law schools

01:58:57.651 --> 01:59:00.929
in America

01:59:00.929 --> 01:59:07.185
that decide the effective decisions

01:59:07.185 --> 01:59:10.399
in legislating the legal market

01:59:10.399 --> 01:59:12.327
in courts

01:59:12.327 --> 01:59:16.835
and we pay them between $300,000 and 500,000.

01:59:16.835 --> 01:59:23.088
while at Yale and Harvard they reduce it to $50,000.

01:59:23.088 --> 01:59:28.323
This is exactly what happened to Islam in the nineteenth century.

01:59:28.323 --> 01:59:36.202
If you look at a professor at Harvard Law School after this,

01:59:36.202 --> 01:59:42.287
who was wealthy, lived in luxury and had a high position,

01:59:42.287 --> 01:59:49.513
will he send his children to the same school?

01:59:49.513 --> 01:59:51.582
No, of course.

01:59:51.582 --> 01:59:54.118
It's fallen.

01:59:54.118 --> 01:59:56.975
They'll send their children to the new and better schools.

01:59:56.975 --> 02:00:00.137
Because they care about their children.

02:00:00.137 --> 02:00:02.342
They are the fruit of your loins.

02:00:02.342 --> 02:00:04.735
You'll send them to the best choice.

02:00:04.735 --> 02:00:08.939
Imagine with me that the schools of jurisprudence have deteriorated

02:00:08.939 --> 02:00:11.188
and it started to fade away.

02:00:11.188 --> 02:00:16.964
To the point where, in 1860 or 1870 at most,

02:00:16.964 --> 02:00:22.583
the last people who wrote in the old jurisprudential way

02:00:22.583 --> 02:00:26.240
and the old style and the old dialectical method

02:00:26.240 --> 02:00:28.820
have stopped.

02:00:28.820 --> 02:00:34.536
And a new style of writing began, which was shallow and lacked depth.

02:00:34.536 --> 02:00:38.172
And knows nothing about the past.

02:00:38.172 --> 02:00:42.879
When there were judges in Egypt in 1920,

02:00:42.879 --> 02:00:48.328
they had problems when they tried to read al-Fiqh

02:00:48.328 --> 02:00:52.124
They struggled to read and comprehend it.

02:00:52.124 --> 02:00:54.702
Here is an exaggerated example:

02:00:54.702 --> 02:01:00.909
When I was young professor,

02:01:00.909 --> 02:01:04.007
without naming any names,

02:01:04.007 --> 02:01:06.303
I met at that time

02:01:06.303 --> 02:01:12.411
the main leader in the Supreme Constitutional Court in Egypt

02:01:12.411 --> 02:01:15.458
we were talking on a street in London.

02:01:15.458 --> 02:01:19.228
He said: I get it,

02:01:19.228 --> 02:01:21.778
but why Shari‘a,

02:01:21.778 --> 02:01:25.749
the Shari‘a people write in incomprehensible codes,

02:01:25.749 --> 02:01:31.184
I can't understand their writings"

02:01:31.184 --> 02:01:35.312
He doesn't understand what al-Fiqh is or how to read it.

02:01:35.312 --> 02:01:39.535
It was so hard for him that he thinks it's written in hieroglyphs.

02:01:39.535 --> 02:01:41.894
I said, It doesn't look like that for me.

02:01:41.894 --> 02:01:44.084
It doesn't look like hieroglyphs.

02:01:44.084 --> 02:01:46.468
I see brilliant logic there.

02:01:46.468 --> 02:01:51.155
This is how the construct of dialectical Islamic jurisprudence makes you feel.

02:01:51.155 --> 02:01:56.731
As we say in Palestine, "yamakhwil alʿaqla" (means eye-opening or mind-blowing)

02:01:56.731 --> 02:02:02.225
This is the effect of the Ottoman state.

02:02:02.225 --> 02:02:05.345
This is a big step of change in quality.

02:02:05.345 --> 02:02:11.087
It didn't just alter the legal and Shari‘a apparatus in the empire,

02:02:11.087 --> 02:02:17.884
but it made it a legal apparatus only and not adherent to Shari‘a.

02:02:17.884 --> 02:02:23.429
Despite all the counterfeiting and confiscations

02:02:23.429 --> 02:02:26.107
from Shari‘a in the personal status law.

02:02:26.107 --> 02:02:29.552
Which has nothing to do with Islamic jurisprudence.

02:02:29.552 --> 02:02:31.469
It was changed a lot.

02:02:31.469 --> 02:02:34.110
They had something called a device of 'talfiq'.

02:02:34.110 --> 02:02:40.087
Talfiq was one of the most important tools for modern reform.

02:02:40.087 --> 02:02:43.994
It originally started in 1917 in the Ottoman Empire.

02:02:43.994 --> 02:02:46.932
It was the Law of Family Rights of 1917

02:02:46.932 --> 02:02:52.360
They even used Shia jurisprudence.

02:02:52.360 --> 02:02:54.985
And they combined it with Maliki jurisprudence

02:02:54.985 --> 02:02:57.239
a few from here and there.

02:02:57.239 --> 02:03:00.000
And they say this is the new law.

02:03:00.000 --> 02:03:02.785
Who decided that? On what basis?

02:03:02.785 --> 02:03:05.557
Which jurist brought all of them together like that?

02:03:05.557 --> 02:03:09.742
That's not important. What is important is what the state decides.

02:03:09.742 --> 02:03:14.517
When you bring those together without explanation or refutation,

02:03:14.517 --> 02:03:16.665
All of al-Fiqh has been refuted.

02:03:16.665 --> 02:03:18.946
Every statement has a refutation.

02:03:18.946 --> 02:03:23.770
And the refutation alone can tell a world about the art of thinking.

02:03:23.770 --> 02:03:25.817
when you read for Al-Nawawi.

02:03:25.817 --> 02:03:28.270
And you see how he objected to al-Shafii.

02:03:28.270 --> 02:03:32.070
Even though you are al-Shafi'i,

02:03:32.070 --> 02:03:36.509
and while your result is correct, the method of refutation is wrong.

02:03:36.509 --> 02:03:39.043
Or maybe it's lacking or incomplete.

02:03:39.043 --> 02:03:41.217
He writes all about it.

02:03:41.217 --> 02:03:45.662
About why did al-Shafi'i not complete this exercise in Fiqh

02:03:45.662 --> 02:03:49.831
that produced the result or statement in question?

02:03:49.831 --> 02:03:51.763
Imagine that.

02:03:51.763 --> 02:03:54.005
This is all gone now.

02:03:54.005 --> 02:03:55.957
No more refutations or anything else.

02:03:55.957 --> 02:03:59.837
That the woman is entitled to such-and-such in the contract of such-and-such.

02:03:59.837 --> 02:04:03.181
This is because we said so.

02:04:03.181 --> 02:04:05.173
OK, where is the logical structure of it?

02:04:05.173 --> 02:04:06.294
It doesn't matter.

02:04:06.294 --> 02:04:10.174
No more diligence, weighting, authentication, or anything like that.

02:04:10.174 --> 02:04:13.027
This is what the state decreed.

02:04:13.027 --> 02:04:16.533
That's why you said that the 19th century

02:04:16.533 --> 02:04:19.143
was a pivotal century in the history of Shari‘a.

02:04:19.143 --> 02:04:22.964
In the late 19th and early 20th centuries,

02:04:22.964 --> 02:04:25.442
 the Ottoman Empire became a modern state.

02:04:25.442 --> 02:04:27.392
It wasn't an Islamic state.

02:04:27.392 --> 02:04:33.364
When I said it was a modern state, it wasn't meant as a complement.

02:04:33.364 --> 02:04:37.919
At the same time, I don't mean modern state as in the temporal sense.

02:04:37.919 --> 02:04:45.046
Modern means an expression of modernity, which is a special qualitative phenomenon.

02:04:45.046 --> 02:04:50.853
Therefore, there is a big difference between the so-called Islamic rule,

02:04:50.853 --> 02:04:53.537
and the so-called modern state.

02:04:53.537 --> 02:04:58.062
This is the subject of the book The Impossible State.

02:04:58.062 --> 02:05:01.794
And you see that there cannot be a modern Islamic state.

02:05:01.794 --> 02:05:06.285
If you mean by modern, the European modernist composition

02:05:06.285 --> 02:05:09.333
because the modern state is a European state.

02:05:09.333 --> 02:05:12.374
Even in China today,

02:05:12.374 --> 02:05:15.179
which is the most creative state

02:05:15.179 --> 02:05:19.340
in creating political and social fields

02:05:19.340 --> 02:05:23.557
from nothing at the beginning

02:05:23.557 --> 02:05:27.996
and later from internal data that is unique to China,

02:05:27.996 --> 02:05:32.700
will not escape the compositions of the modern state.

02:05:32.700 --> 02:05:36.183
Since we are at modernity

02:05:36.183 --> 02:05:38.612
or the modern state,

02:05:38.612 --> 02:05:40.738
I want to talk about the concept of modernity.

02:05:40.738 --> 02:05:43.221
You said: The solution to the problem of modernity

02:05:43.221 --> 02:05:47.183
is to understand how everything is related to everything else.

02:05:47.183 --> 02:05:49.753
- Because everything is interconnected.
- (Correct.)

02:05:49.753 --> 02:05:52.710
Could you elaborate?

02:05:52.710 --> 02:05:55.097
Let me ask you this question:

02:05:55.097 --> 02:06:00.543
What is one of the most important ways to rule

02:06:00.543 --> 02:06:03.518
a land that has different tribes?

02:06:03.518 --> 02:06:08.389
When the English went to America,

02:06:08.389 --> 02:06:12.479
what was their most important weapon to control the land?

02:06:12.479 --> 02:06:17.444
They allied with some tribes

02:06:17.444 --> 02:06:20.849
who they tempt with something

02:06:20.849 --> 02:06:26.683
to help them wage war against their other sister tribes.

02:06:26.683 --> 02:06:30.882
It's called the divide and conquer strategy.

02:06:30.882 --> 02:06:37.606
Dividing something is one of the most effective means of control.

02:06:37.606 --> 02:06:40.029
If you face 20 people at once,

02:06:40.029 --> 02:06:43.369
the example is very clear but this is only to show its importance,

02:06:43.369 --> 02:06:45.737
you'll lose to them.

02:06:45.737 --> 02:06:48.534
If you isolated them and took them one by one,

02:06:48.534 --> 02:06:54.057
and you are strong enough, you'll finish them all.

02:06:54.057 --> 02:06:57.477
Modernity

02:06:57.477 --> 02:07:01.574
Its main goal started, continued and still continues

02:07:01.574 --> 02:07:04.195
according to the logic of control.

02:07:04.195 --> 02:07:06.241
The control of everything.

02:07:06.241 --> 02:07:09.094
And the most important thing is to control nature.

02:07:09.094 --> 02:07:12.115
However, since man is a part of nature,

02:07:12.115 --> 02:07:15.446
it becomes about man's dominance over man.

02:07:15.446 --> 02:07:22.768
As I said in 'Restating Orientalism',

02:07:22.768 --> 02:07:29.666
Europe colonized itself before it colonized the world.

02:07:29.666 --> 02:07:31.457
How?

02:07:31.457 --> 02:07:35.851
It entered into a European self-transformation project.

02:07:35.851 --> 02:07:38.163
From a religious self

02:07:38.163 --> 02:07:42.275
and of course, Europe had more problems than anywhere else in the world,

02:07:42.275 --> 02:07:46.985
because Christianity in Europe was rotten.

02:07:46.985 --> 02:07:49.624
It was corrupt and cruel.

02:07:49.624 --> 02:07:52.226
It wasn't a true religion.

02:07:52.226 --> 02:07:54.953
Religion must be tolerant and compassionate

02:07:54.953 --> 02:07:58.117
Christianity in Europe was very violent.

02:07:58.117 --> 02:08:01.441
I don't blame Europeans

02:08:01.441 --> 02:08:04.492
for wanting to get out of

02:08:04.492 --> 02:08:08.688
the Christian era and the Caesarean era.

